stylometry: One probability distribution is discrete.  The discrete probability distribution deals with the likelihood or the probability of that event happening.  For instance if you are rolling dice there is a certain probability that a 2 and 5 will come up.  There is a certain number of possible outcomes based on the problem you are dealing with.  A discrete probability would be used in order for a cmpany to determine what the chances are of a certain simulation occuring based on the total amount probable .  They will be able to see what the level of risk would be for them to chose one of the possibilities.
